Delshad walked out of her house in a slump. His shoulders went down every time he left her presence. It made him feel drained. If only he could reach her somehow, he felt as if everything would be all right. Only problem was that she couldn't ask for help. He shrugged; the priests had been telling him that no one can be helped unless they want to be. Even healing didn't work on those who didn't want to be healed, and charms wouldn't work on those who didn't, in the very most miniscule least, want to be.<br>
<br>
He thought about the way she'd been acting lately. He knew that Cealestis(I FINALLY GOT IT RIGHT, WOO!) was more of a @#%$ ingrate than she'd like to admit, ore maybe she already knew that... Why someone would subject themselves to such torture was beyond Delshad. He just wished there was some way to make her happy, to make her see... But none of it mattered. It wouldn't happen; nothing mattered.<br>
<br>
Time for more sparring. I can't take this sitting around bullshitt. To the guildhouse. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A> at: 7/10/02 10:47:17 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/usuedydar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Suedydar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of Souls</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/02 10:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Black Rainbow</span><hr size=1> ((Bleh, Mindles beat me to Delshad! &gt;.&lt; Oh well..I'll go think of someone for Miiam to kill...))<br>
