<br>
What? He... he caught the counterattack! How did he....?<br>
<br>
No matter. The ranger tapped Delshad's own blade to the left, and the warrior-in-training spun towards the blade, counter-clockwise, and brought the mace in his right hand up high, to knock the elf's head off. Quick, that ranger.<br>
<br>
The elf ducked, and came up towards Delshad's chest with both his war blades together in an X. Delshad dropped his mace, and dropped down, arching his back, and allowing the blades to come up harmlessly without contacting. From the position of two legs and a left hand on the ground, he thrust his legs forward, putting all his weight on his left hand. As his legs went to the outside of the elf's, it looked down, and his eyes widened in fear as Delshad legs close around his own, and as the warrior pulled back, never touching the ground, he brought the elf's legs out from under him with Delshad's own.<br>
<br>
On his back, the ranger crossed his blades up in an X to stop a killing blow from Delshad. His foot was brought up, and he kicked Delshad a few yards back in the arena. The elf was already on his feet by the time Delshad was up again. He charged, roaring in rage.<br>
<br>
With fluid arm movements, Delshad pressed harder and harder on the ranger's blades. Each parry was nearly faulty, and after a few attempts at blocking the mace, the elf's primary blade was sent flying. The elf chanted a few words as he backed away from the onslaught of Delshad's weapons. Roots sprang up, and entangled his feet. Nearly falling on his face, Delshad watched the elf pull a bow from half the arena away. Delshad ducked one well-placed arrow that would have killed him, and launched his mace. It smacked the elf directly between the eyes, and Delshad immediatley cut the vines loose.<br>
<br>
He charged full speed, and let his left shoulder be thrown back as flames slammed into it. No more chanting elf.... you're MINE! Delshad grabbed the elf's other hand to still his blade, and bashed him in the mouth to prevent chanting. Delshad's short sword came up and bit into his stomach. &quot;TIME!&quot; called the referee.<br>
<br>
&quot;TIME! *TIME*!!!&quot; Delshad screamed in rage. &quot;*NOW* YOU CALL TIME!? How about when he used MAGIC, HUH? That was a PENALTY! And what about aiming for my KNEECAPS!?&quot;<br>
<br>
The burly elf in a striped tunic growled, &quot;I. Said. *Time*.&quot; Delshad threw down the training weapons and casted off the arena plate mail. Stupid elves. If it was a human, he'd have won a *LOT* sooner...<br>
