before he noticed the blood dripped slowly from his busted nose.  Quickly, he tore a strip of cloth from his shirt, worn so thin he swore he could see through it.  With a shrug, he placed it on the wound hoping the drying blood would serve as an adhesive for the bandage.  Life really sucks. <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 4:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/Reineva.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Black Rainbow</span><hr size=1> Miriam taps her feet on the always wet ground. It was getting colder and Aino *still* did not show. Probably out with her new loser boyfriend. She was such a @#%$ hoe. This guy this week, this guy next week. She'd led them on till they begged for her, and then leave them faster than a fat woman leaves a fat free buffet. With a sigh Miriam looks around again. No Aino. A boy crosses the street a few yards away from her. Miriam squints her eyes. It was Caelstis's little brother, Saeran. Something was wrong with his nose? ... Cupping her hands around her mouth she shouts, &quot;Hay cutie, ya feelin lucky?&quot; She giggled and wrapped her arms around herself. Damn it was cold.  <p><Br> <Br> <Br> <Br> Your head will collapse <Br> But there's nothing in it <Br> And you'll ask yourself <Br> Where is my mind? <Br> Where is my mind? <Br> Wheeeeeere iiis my mind?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard